{
  "texts": [
    "Integration with histology images.",
    "Although histology hematoxylinand-eosin (H&E) images are usually provided along with ST data (for example, the commercial Visium platform), current methods fail to use such modality in deconvolving cell types.",
    "Histology, however, provides useful information about morphology, tissue structure, cell density and spatial dependency of cells.",
    "Integrating histology and transcriptomes in a joint model is challenging, as the two data modalities are very different: the genome-level transcripts are high-dimensional vectors, whereas the histology data consist of multichannel images.",
    "Thus, it is essential to address the mismatch of these two types of data while preserving cell type-specific information of gene expression and cell morphology-specific information of histology images."
  ]
}